<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I am a Necro part time PK</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Benign">Benign</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:00 p.m. 30/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I am a Necro part time PK<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2224" TARGET=_self>Can anyone confirm these? XP Loss to DOT and pet death?</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>XP loss for pets is a fact(no explaination necessary). DoT XP loss is a little different though. Sometimes people lose XP sometimes they don't. To make someone lose XP you hit them with a low damage DoT and have them get close enough to dying where they bleed to death. If the DoT damage itself kills you, you will not lose XP(although you will lose yer cash and an item). Now while all classes can bleed someone to death by punching them into bleeding to death, the DoT casters are definately more adept. I have seen Necros and Druids do it, although I suppose Shamans could as well.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
